<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>
Mixe-Zoque Language Family
</H1>



The Mixe-Zoque languages, Mixe, Zoque, and Popoluca, have not been definitively linked with any of the larger 
Mesoamerican language families. 
<BR><BR>
<b><U>Sponsored Links</U></b><BR>
<script type="text/javascript">
    google_ad_client = "ca-pub-8872632675285158";
    google_ad_slot = "7933889216";
    google_ad_width = 336;
    google_ad_height = 280;
</script>
<!-- ATF large bordered ad -->
<script type="text/javascript"
src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">
</script>

<BR><BR>
Mixe-Zoque languages are spoken in Mexico and include:
<BR><BR>

<DIR>
<LI><a href="http://www.native-languages.org/mixe.htm">Mixe</a>
<LI><a href="http://www.native-languages.org/zoque.htm">Zoque</a>
<LI><a href="http://www.native-languages.org/popoluca.htm">Popoluca</a>
</dir>
     
